pageContext.claim: “Then I see polls come out. We had one come out today. Rasmussen. Forty-seven [percent]. Forty-six or 47. And you know, 47 you can't lose. That's a very high number. In fact Obama got out at 46, I guess.”
pageContext.analysis: Trump had a 41 percent approval rating in the Rasmussen poll -- which gave Obama a 62 percent approval when he left office.
